title: Japanese stocks have been hitting record highs. But the rally may be 'fragile'
summary_full: Japan's Nikkei 225 has notched several firsts in recent days, crossing 56,000, then 57,000 and nearing 58,000, fueled by the so-called "Takaichi trade."
